                <head>107. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 13, 1962, <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">McGeorge Bundy</persName>
                    transmitted National Security Action Memorandum 131 to various Executive Agency
                    Directors. It detailed a series of training objectives for counterinsurgency.
                    For text of this memorandum, see <hi rend="italic">United States-Vietnam
                        Relations, 1945-1967</hi>, Book 11, pages 467-469.</p>
            </div>
